00:15:52.617 --> 00:15:54.552
MIKE: A military base?

251
00:15:54.586 --> 00:15:55.988
DEBBIE: No!

252
00:16:01.960 --> 00:16:03.328
The shooting star.

253
00:16:03.362 --> 00:16:04.596
What are you
talking about?

254
00:16:04.630 --> 00:16:06.966
The shooting star we went
to go look for. we are in it.

255
00:16:09.535 --> 00:16:11.036
What was that?

256
00:16:11.070 --> 00:16:12.171
I don't know.

257
00:16:15.173 --> 00:16:16.841
but it's coming this way.

258
00:16:16.875 --> 00:16:18.377
Here. Come on.

259
00:16:36.394 --> 00:16:38.130
Look at this place.

260
00:16:41.733 --> 00:16:44.836
It smells like candy.

261
00:16:44.869 --> 00:16:47.205
You know.
I don't know what
we saw out there before.

262
00:16:47.238 --> 00:16:51.276
but this
looks like a cotton
candy factory to me.

263
00:16:52.777 --> 00:16:54.546
Yeah.

264
00:16:54.579 --> 00:16:56.514
This must be where
they hang it up to dry

265
00:16:56.548 --> 00:16:58.751
before they
ship the stuff out.

266
00:16:58.784 --> 00:17:00.786
No. it's not.

267
00:17:00.819 --> 00:17:03.589
I've never seen anything
like this before. have you?

268
00:17:04.289 --> 00:17:05.356
No.

269
00:17:05.390 --> 00:17:07.426
That's because nobody has.

270
00:17:09.727 --> 00:17:12.297
I don't believe in UFOs.

271
00:17:12.329 --> 00:17:17.067
but if they do exist.
then we're trapped
in one right now.

272
00:17:17.101 --> 00:17:20.405
Just calm down. There's got
to be a logical explanation
for this.

273
00:17:20.439 --> 00:17:21.974
This isn't what
you think it is.

274
00:17:23.742 --> 00:17:27.179
Nobody stores
cotton candy like this.

275
00:17:27.212 --> 00:17:29.615
What are you
talking about?
Of course it is.

276
00:17:30.181 --> 00:17:31.282
Look.

277
00:17:31.316 --> 00:17:32.684
(SCREAMS)

278
00:18:13.792 --> 00:18:15.294
Joe Lombardo.

279
00:18:27.139 --> 00:18:28.640
Down this way.

280
00:18:47.325 --> 00:18:48.527
MIKE: Are you okay?

281
00:18:48.560 --> 00:18:49.627
I think so.

282
00:18:49.661 --> 00:18:51.062
Come on.

283
00:18:51.096 --> 00:18:52.764
DEBBIE:
Popcorn?
Why popcorn?

284
00:18:52.797 --> 00:18:55.033
MIKE: Because they're clowns.
that's why.

285
00:18:56.501 --> 00:18:58.704
(SPEAKING IN ALIEN LANGUAGE)

286
00:19:10.415 --> 00:19:12.084
(BALLOON SNIFFING)

287
00:19:13.818 --> 00:19:15.487
(BALLOON BARKING)

288
00:19:25.030 --> 00:19:26.798
(DEBBIE SCREAMS)

289
00:19:26.831 --> 00:19:28.600
(BALLOON BARKING)

290
00:19:30.568 --> 00:19:31.870
Mike. get me out of here!

291
00:19:35.673 --> 00:19:36.942
(HOWLING)

292
00:19:38.142 --> 00:19:40.312
DEBBIE: Hurry.
they're coming!

293
00:19:47.920 --> 00:19:49.188
(SCREAMS)

294
00:20:11.576 --> 00:20:13.044
DEBBIE: We have
to tell the police.

295
00:20:13.078 --> 00:20:15.013
Yeah. we're gonna run
to the police station.
we're gonna tell them

296
00:20:15.047 --> 00:20:16.381
there's
a bunch of clowns
running around the hill

297
00:20:16.415 --> 00:20:18.016
killing people
with cotton candy?

298
00:20:18.049 --> 00:20:21.953
I have a friend there.
I know he'll believe us.

299
00:20:21.987 --> 00:20:24.089
I don't know. Debbie.
I wouldn't even
believe us.

300
00:20:34.866 --> 00:20:37.069
(SPEAKING IN ALIEN LANGUAGE)

301
00:20:59.057 --> 00:21:00.926
(TIRES SCREECHING)

302
00:21:02.794 --> 00:21:04.296
What the heck?

303
00:21:06.331 --> 00:21:07.833
(CAR HORN BLARING)

304
00:21:11.503 --> 00:21:13.338
(GLASS SHATTERING)

305
00:21:13.372 --> 00:21:15.841
Dave! Oh. my God!
Something horrible
has happened!

306
00:21:15.874 --> 00:21:16.908
Somebody's been killed!

307
00:21:16.942 --> 00:21:18.242
Wait a second. Debbie!
What happened?

308
00:21:18.276 --> 00:21:19.878
You gotta help us!
We gotta do something!

309
00:21:19.911 --> 00:21:19.911
There are two people dead!

310
00:21:19.911 --> 00:21:21.813
Who. Debbie? Who's dead?

311
00:21:21.846 --> 00:21:22.914
Joe Lombardo. He's dead.

312
00:21:22.947 --> 00:21:24.382
And some old man. too.

313
00:21:24.415 --> 00:21:25.950
Wait a second. guys.
Are you sure about this?

314
00:21:25.984 --> 00:21:29.854
Yes! They were hanging in
there wrapped up in these
cotton candy things.

315
00:21:29.887 --> 00:21:31.356
these cocoons.

316
00:21:31.389 --> 00:21:32.490
Cocoons?

317
00:21:32.524 --> 00:21:33.859
Yes. cocoons.

318
00:21:33.892 --> 00:21:34.993
You know. cocoons.

319
00:21:35.026 --> 00:21:37.228
All right. all right.
everybody calm down.

320
00:21:37.262 --> 00:21:39.397
Look. Debbie.
come inside and
explain this to me.

321
00:21:39.430 --> 00:21:40.798
I'd like to help you.
but before I can.

322
00:21:40.832 --> 00:21:42.601
I've got to understand
what's going on here
myself.

323
00:21:55.513 --> 00:21:59.450
WOMAN: I really need
to get some mascara.
okay?

324
00:21:59.484 --> 00:22:01.752
Okay.
why don't we just
go to the drugstore?

325
00:22:01.786 --> 00:22:03.889
Okay?
And then we'll go on.

326
00:22:06.190 --> 00:22:07.292
Look.

327
00:22:13.497 --> 00:22:14.599
Cute.

328
00:22:21.239 --> 00:22:22.708
(SPEAKING IN ALIEN LANGUAGE)

329
00:22:23.341 --> 00:22:25.577
All right. sit down.

330
00:22:25.610 --> 00:22:27.912
Let's start from the
beginning. all right?

331
00:22:27.946 --> 00:22:31.283
Okay. We were up at
the "Top of the World."

332
00:22:31.316 --> 00:22:33.418
and we saw
this shooting star.

333
00:22:33.451 --> 00:22:35.286
and we decided
to go look for it.

334
00:22:35.319 --> 00:22:38.657
But instead of finding the
shooting star. we saw this
circus tent.

335
00:22:38.690 --> 00:22:41.459
That's when we went inside.
and that is when we saw
all those people

336
00:22:41.492 --> 00:22:44.529
in those pink
cotton candy cocoons.

337
00:22:44.562 --> 00:22:47.632
Dave. it was
not a circus tent.
It was something else.

338
00:22:47.665 --> 00:22:47.665
What? What?

339
00:22:47.665 --> 00:22:49.467
MIKE: It was a spaceship.

340
00:22:49.500 --> 00:22:52.270
and there
was these things.
these killer clowns.

341
00:22:52.303 --> 00:22:54.939
and they
shot popcorn at us.
We barely got away.

342
00:22:54.973 --> 00:22:56.308
(WHISTLES)

343
00:22:58.276 --> 00:23:00.545
Killer clowns
from outer space?

344
00:23:01.579 --> 00:23:03.281
Holy shit.

345
00:23:03.315 --> 00:23:06.485
Dave. we are
telling you the truth.
You've got to believe us.

346
00:23:06.518 --> 00:23:08.186
Let me tell you
something. honey.

347
00:23:08.219 --> 00:23:11.222
I was just over there.
There's nothing going on.

348
00:23:11.256 --> 00:23:13.691
Excuse me. please.
but we're talking
to Dave.

349
00:23:13.725 --> 00:23:16.460
Yeah. just hold on a second.
Mooney. They say some
people are dead.

350
00:23:16.494 --> 00:23:17.528
Let's hear them out.

351
00:23:17.562 --> 00:23:18.897
All right. Dave.

352
00:23:19.664 --> 00:23:20.732
Okay.

353
00:23:20.765 --> 00:23:22.733
Clowns. cotton candy.

354
00:23:22.767 --> 00:23:24.602
flying popcorn.

355
00:23:24.636 --> 00:23:28.039
Go ahead.
Let them make fools out
of the police department.

356
00:23:28.072 --> 00:23:29.640
I told you.
I was just over there!

357
00:23:29.674 --> 00:23:31.142
Who are you
going to believe?
Me or this little tramp?

358
00:23:31.175 --> 00:23:33.210
Now. come on. Mooney!

359
00:23:33.244 --> 00:23:35.414
I'm handling this.
all right?

360
00:23:38.516 --> 00:23:41.987
All right. Debbie.
who's your friend?

361
00:23:42.020 --> 00:23:44.122
DEBBIE: Mike.
We go to school together.

362
00:23:44.155 --> 00:23:46.625
You two were up at
"Top of the World"
together?

363
00:23:47.658 --> 00:23:48.760
Yeah.

364
00:23:49.760 --> 00:23:52.297
I know you.
you little fart.

365
00:23:52.330 --> 00:23:54.966
You hang out with
the Terenzi brothers.

366
00:23:55.700 --> 00:23:58.670
Clowns? I get it.

367
00:23:58.703 --> 00:24:01.973
Another one of their stupid
stunts to sell ice cream
from that goddamn truck

368
00:24:02.006 --> 00:24:04.041
those hoodlums run around in.

369
00:24:04.075 --> 00:24:06.011
Well. now I really
believe this.

370
00:24:06.044 --> 00:24:10.181
Well.
you better go now. Dave.
before the clowns take over.

371
00:24:10.214 --> 00:24:11.783
and when you get back
from saving the world.

372
00:24:11.816 --> 00:24:14.052
I want a full written
report so I can give
it to the chief

373
00:24:14.085 --> 00:24:15.787
when he gets back on Monday.

374
00:24:15.821 --> 00:24:18.256
(LAUGHING)

375
00:24:18.289 --> 00:24:20.525
Look.
everything happened
just the way we said.

376
00:24:20.558 --> 00:24:22.327
We are telling you the truth.

377
00:24:22.360 --> 00:24:24.663
All right.
You two come with me.

378
00:24:25.396 --> 00:24:26.430
Come on.

379
00:24:26.464 --> 00:24:29.201
Hurry up. Dave.
Don't let them
get away.

380
00:24:30.235 --> 00:24:31.770
Go ahead. Dave.

381
00:24:32.871 --> 00:24:35.974
make a dummy
out of yourself.

382
00:24:36.007 --> 00:24:38.143
But you're not going
to make a dummy out of me.

383
00:24:40.678 --> 00:24:42.314
You. in the back.

384
00:26:00.791 --> 00:26:02.193
(SHOUTING)

385
00:26:05.897 --> 00:26:07.766
(LAUGHING EVILLY)

386
00:26:12.770 --> 00:26:13.838
Excuse me.

387
00:26:15.106 --> 00:26:16.407
Oh. my.

388
00:26:16.441 --> 00:26:17.976
May I help you?

389
00:26:24.849 --> 00:26:25.884
No!

390
00:26:47.605 --> 00:26:48.640
No.

391
00:26:53.411 --> 00:26:55.479
DAVE:
All right. we're going
up there to check this out.

392
00:26:55.513 --> 00:26:57.047
First. I'm taking you home.
Debbie.

393
00:26:57.081 --> 00:26:59.784
No way.
I'm going back
up there with you.

394
00:26:59.817 --> 00:27:01.619
You can't tell me
what to do.

395
00:27:01.652 --> 00:27:03.188
Debbie. just listen to me.
would you?

396
00:27:03.221 --> 00:27:07.625
I don't have to listen to you.
You are not my boyfriend
anymore. all right?

397
00:27:07.659 --> 00:27:10.661
DAVE: Yeah. that's right.
I'm not your boyfriend
anymore.

398
00:27:10.695 --> 00:27:12.730
That doesn't
change the way I feel
about you. little Debbie.

399
00:27:12.763 --> 00:27:14.566
DEBBIE: Dave. please.

400
00:27:15.332 --> 00:27:17.301
Don't do this to me.

401
00:27:17.335 --> 00:27:19.337
All right. Debbie.
you got a choice.

402
00:27:19.370 --> 00:27:21.405
Either go home. or I'm gonna
take you back to the station

403
00:27:21.438 --> 00:27:23.274
and lock you up
for safekeeping.
How's that?

404
00:27:25.210 --> 00:27:26.811
(DOORBELL RINGS)

405
00:27:28.179 --> 00:27:29.414
Pizza!

406
00:27:32.250 --> 00:27:33.418
Pizza.

407
00:27:40.958 --> 00:27:42.594
(LAUGHING EVILLY)

408
00:27:47.032 --> 00:27:48.633
(DOORBELL RINGS)

409
00:27:51.669 --> 00:27:52.904
(EXCLAIMS)

410
00:27:53.237 --> 00:27:54.539
For me?

411
00:27:57.141 --> 00:28:01.012
Oh. Jim.
is this from you?

412
00:28:11.923 --> 00:28:13.858
Look. Debbie...

413
00:28:13.891 --> 00:28:16.327
May I please speak
to Mike outside?

414
00:28:17.862 --> 00:28:19.230
Fine. Sure.

415
00:28:20.365 --> 00:28:21.700
Thank you.

416
00:28:30.541 --> 00:28:32.010
Your old boyfriend?
This is great.

417
00:28:32.043 --> 00:28:32.043
This is just great.

418
00:28:32.043 --> 00:28:33.778
Will you come here?

419
00:28:36.147 --> 00:28:38.283
He's probably gonna take me
up on top of the hill and
shoot me.

420
00:28:38.316 --> 00:28:40.451
Look. don't worry
about Dave.

421
00:28:40.485 --> 00:28:43.921
It's those clowns
you got to worry about.

422
00:28:43.954 --> 00:28:46.224
Listen. as soon as
you guys leave here.

423
00:28:46.257 --> 00:28:48.025
I'm going to follow
you guys up there.

424
00:28:48.059 --> 00:28:49.326
You're going to
follow us up there?

425
00:28:49.360 --> 00:28:51.896
Debbie. I don't even
want to go up there.

426
00:28:51.929 --> 00:28:54.231
Listen. you stay
inside the house and
keep the door locked.

427
00:28:54.265 --> 00:28:56.434
I'll be back here in
a little bit to
check on you.

428
00:28:57.902 --> 00:28:59.003
Okay?

429
00:29:00.838 --> 00:29:02.373
You better.

430
00:29:11.983 --> 00:29:13.718
That's good timing.

431
00:29:18.156 --> 00:29:19.657
(CAR STARTING)

432
00:29:45.650 --> 00:29:46.818
Cream.

433
00:29:51.255 --> 00:29:52.690
(GROANING)

434
00:30:09.006 --> 00:30:11.042
(SNEEZES)

435
00:30:19.617 --> 00:30:21.119
Wait a minute.

436
00:30:22.053 --> 00:30:23.487
Where is it?

437
00:30:23.521 --> 00:30:24.988
Yeah. that's what
I'd like to know. pal.

438
00:30:25.022 --> 00:30:26.690
MIKE: It was right there
where that hole is.

439
00:30:26.724 --> 00:30:28.092
DAVE: So you're saying
that hole is where
the tent was?

440
00:30:28.126 --> 00:30:29.794
The tent made that hole.
is that what you're
telling me?

441
00:30:29.827 --> 00:30:31.562
Yes! It was there.

442
00:30:31.596 --> 00:30:32.797
Look. we saw it.
That's a fact.

443
00:30:32.830 --> 00:30:34.699
I'll tell you what
the facts are. mister.

444
00:30:34.732 --> 00:30:37.268
You said
people are being killed.
Now. where are the bodies?

445
00:30:37.301 --> 00:30:39.203
I don't know.
I saw Joe Lombardo dead.

446
00:30:39.236 --> 00:30:40.572
I can only tell you
what I think I saw.

447
00:30:40.605 --> 00:30:42.306
Oh. so now you
just think you saw?

448
00:30:42.340 --> 00:30:45.343
No. I know what I saw.
I just can't prove it.
My proof is gone.

449
00:30:45.376 --> 00:30:46.444
Yeah. right.
Turn around. pal.

450
00:30:48.279 --> 00:30:51.616
Mooney was right. huh?
Got nothing better to
do than cause problems.

451
00:30:51.649 --> 00:30:52.917
Well. you're not gonna
get away with it this time.

452
00:30:52.950 --> 00:30:55.753
Get away with what?
Debbie saw it. too.

453
00:30:55.787 --> 00:30:57.554
Yes. she did. didn't she?

454
00:30:57.588 --> 00:30:58.823
Come on.

455
00:31:03.227 --> 00:31:05.162
Hey. Eddie. is that
a new bike you got?

456
00:31:05.196 --> 00:31:06.564
WOMAN: What's
happening. Spike?

457
00:31:14.138 --> 00:31:15.874
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

458
00:31:19.877 --> 00:31:22.614
Big bad Jojo
comin' into town.

459
00:31:24.014 --> 00:31:25.049
Watch this. baby.

460
00:31:25.082 --> 00:31:26.584
Is that bike
too big for you?

461
00:31:26.617 --> 00:31:27.785
Patty!

462
00:31:31.488 --> 00:31:32.656
Mean bike
you got there.

463
00:31:32.690 --> 00:31:34.025
MAN: Yeah.

464
00:31:36.260 --> 00:31:39.197
Can I take a ride. pal?

465
00:31:42.332 --> 00:31:44.102
Can I beep the horn?

466
00:31:47.304 --> 00:31:48.673
Thank you!

467
00:31:55.312 --> 00:31:57.582
He should've let
the man ride his bike.

468
00:31:59.317 --> 00:32:00.818
(HORN HONKING)

469
00:32:02.587 --> 00:32:04.288
I'm sorry.

470
00:32:04.321 --> 00:32:06.758
I seem to have
broken your bike.

471
00:32:07.057 --> 00:32:08.293
(CRYING)

472
00:32:11.996 --> 00:32:13.531
Where'd he go?

473
00:32:15.533 --> 00:32:17.702
(SPEAKING IN ALIEN LANGUAGE)

474
00:32:25.142 --> 00:32:26.577
(LAUGHING)

475
00:32:27.578 --> 00:32:30.882
What are
you going to do.
knock my block off?

476
00:32:31.682 --> 00:32:33.051
(SCREAMING)

477
00:32:33.417 --> 00:32:34.686
Damn!

478
00:32:36.954 --> 00:32:38.455
WOMAN: Come on.
let's get out of here!

479
00:32:38.489 --> 00:32:39.557
Come on. guys!

480
00:32:39.590 --> 00:32:41.058
WOMAN: Get me out of here!

481
00:32:41.091 --> 00:32:43.161
(LAUGHING EVILLY)

482
00:32:50.067 --> 00:32:52.803
Here's some
more ketchup for
your French fries.

483
00:32:52.837 --> 00:32:53.871
Now here's
some more ketchup.

484
00:32:53.905 --> 00:32:57.007
I want you
to sit still and
eat your hamburger.

485
00:32:57.041 --> 00:32:59.443
This isn't as much
fun as it used to be.

486
00:32:59.477 --> 00:33:01.045
It is
if you're
the winners.

487
00:34:02.873 --> 00:34:04.008
WOMAN: Back here.
young lady.

488
00:34:04.041 --> 00:34:06.010
You're not going anywhere
until you finish your food.

489
00:34:27.231 --> 00:34:28.833
What's going on?

490
00:36:12.503 --> 00:36:14.238
All right. get out.

491
00:36:17.508 --> 00:36:19.176
Turn around.

492
00:36:19.210 --> 00:36:22.079
What are you doing. man?
You're not going to
hit me. are you?

493
00:36:22.113 --> 00:36:23.714
Just turn around. pal.
all right?

494
00:36:23.748 --> 00:36:25.115
Look. I'm sorry
about Debbie.
but I...

495
00:36:25.148 --> 00:36:26.884
Just drop it. Mike!

496
00:36:31.888 --> 00:36:33.424
Check this out.

497
00:36:34.224 --> 00:36:35.692
That's the stuff.

498
00:36:35.725 --> 00:36:37.061
That's the stuff that
I was telling you about

499
00:36:37.094 --> 00:36:39.096
that was
all wrapped
around Joe Lombardo.

500
00:36:39.129 --> 00:36:40.164
Where'd you get that?

501
00:36:40.197 --> 00:36:42.533
Over in that jeep
