(DEBBIE SCREAMS)

750
00:59:36.939 --> 00:59:38.474
Debbie! Debbie! Debbie!

751
00:59:40.109 --> 00:59:41.878
(DRILL SOUNDING)

752
00:59:46.181 --> 00:59:47.517
(SCREAMS)

753
00:59:53.189 --> 00:59:54.857
(SCREAMING)

754
00:59:54.891 --> 00:59:56.225
(LAUGHING)

755
01:00:20.983 --> 01:00:23.186
 (POP GOES THE WEASEL PLAYING)

756
01:00:25.220 --> 01:00:26.923
MIKE: Okay. see this
white house over here?

757
01:00:26.956 --> 01:00:28.457
Take a right...
I mean. a left right here.

758
01:00:28.490 --> 01:00:28.490
RICH: A left?

759
01:00:28.490 --> 01:00:29.525
MIKE: Right.

760
01:00:29.558 --> 01:00:29.558
RICH: Right.

761
01:00:29.558 --> 01:00:31.027
No. left! Left!

762
01:00:40.035 --> 01:00:42.071
The house right up...

763
01:00:43.472 --> 01:00:45.541
Holy shit.
What is that?

764
01:00:53.115 --> 01:00:54.783
Look at that.

765
01:00:54.817 --> 01:00:55.918
Mike!

766
01:01:01.557 --> 01:01:03.926
Come on. we can't lose them!
They got Debbie!

767
01:01:18.741 --> 01:01:20.076
Hey. Mike!

768
01:01:29.185 --> 01:01:31.487
Come on. Rich.
we're losing them. Can't
you go a little bit faster?

769
01:01:31.520 --> 01:01:33.589
Come on. Mike.
what do you want?
This is an ice cream truck.

770
01:01:47.603 --> 01:01:49.572
Hey. Rich. the cops!
Stop the truck!

771
01:01:54.143 --> 01:01:56.411
Shit. Rich.
now you did it.

772
01:01:56.445 --> 01:01:58.247
I did?
What do you mean?
You told me to stop.

773
01:01:58.281 --> 01:01:59.448
I didn't.
I told you
to pull over.

774
01:01:59.481 --> 01:02:00.816
No. you didn't.
You said stop.
so I stopped.

775
01:02:00.849 --> 01:02:01.984
I meant pull over.

776
01:02:02.017 --> 01:02:04.386
If you meant pull over.
you should have said
pull over.

777
01:02:04.419 --> 01:02:06.288
Why don't you say
what you mean
next time.

778
01:02:06.321 --> 01:02:08.091
RICH: Come on. let's
go see what happened.

779
01:02:11.960 --> 01:02:13.930
MIKE: Dave.
are you okay?

780
01:02:15.497 --> 01:02:18.067
God. Fuck.

781
01:02:18.100 --> 01:02:19.635
What the hell
are you guys doing?

782
01:02:19.668 --> 01:02:21.270
They got Debbie.

783
01:02:22.371 --> 01:02:24.240
Get in the truck. pal.

784
01:02:26.409 --> 01:02:29.812
Gee. Officer.
I'm really sorry. I was
feeling a little queasy.

785
01:02:29.845 --> 01:02:31.213
Hey. Mike. which way
were they heading?

786
01:02:31.246 --> 01:02:32.547
They went that way.
but now we lost them.

787
01:02:32.581 --> 01:02:34.083
I don't know
where they went.

788
01:02:34.116 --> 01:02:36.885
DAVE: I do.
If you were a clown.
where would you hide?

789
01:02:36.919 --> 01:02:38.120
MIKE: The amusement park!

790
01:02:38.153 --> 01:02:38.153
PAUL: Great!

791
01:02:38.153 --> 01:02:39.856
RICH: All right!

792
01:03:13.589 --> 01:03:16.726
The park's closed.
I'll have to ask
you to leave.

793
01:03:48.824 --> 01:03:51.060
What are you going to
do with those pies. boys?

794
01:04:08.210 --> 01:04:10.346
(SPEAKING IN ALIEN LANGUAGE)

795
01:04:41.843 --> 01:04:43.312
(EXCLAIMS)

796
01:04:43.345 --> 01:04:44.580
Everybody stick together.

797
01:04:48.450 --> 01:04:49.851
She's gone.

798
01:04:49.885 --> 01:04:52.655
RICH: (EXCLAIMS) Hey.
you guys. this is weird.

799
01:04:54.724 --> 01:04:56.258
Look at this stuff.

800
01:04:56.291 --> 01:04:58.660
Looks like a wad
of melted ice cream.

801
01:04:58.694 --> 01:05:00.195
DAVE: Yeah. well. it's not.

802
01:05:00.229 --> 01:05:01.597
MIKE: Oh. shit.

803
01:05:02.330 --> 01:05:03.632
Yeah.

804
01:05:03.666 --> 01:05:05.167
DAVE: Come on.

805
01:05:19.949 --> 01:05:22.852
Mike.
you take this
and follow me.

806
01:05:22.885 --> 01:05:25.421
All right.
now. you guys.
no fooling around.

807
01:05:25.454 --> 01:05:27.722
Stick together. okay?

808
01:05:27.756 --> 01:05:29.692
I don't know
what the hell's in here.

809
01:05:38.633 --> 01:05:41.070
(EXCLAIMS) Scary!

810
01:05:42.137 --> 01:05:43.773
MIKE: Dave. did you
get through for help?

811
01:05:43.806 --> 01:05:46.308
DAVE: Yeah. yeah.
help is on the way.

812
01:05:46.341 --> 01:05:48.710
MIKE: You tell them
it was an invasion?

813
01:05:48.743 --> 01:05:51.480
DAVE: I told them.
but I don't really
believe it myself.

814
01:05:51.513 --> 01:05:53.182
Where did they
come from?

815
01:05:53.215 --> 01:05:56.017
Why are they here?
Why clowns?

816
01:05:56.051 --> 01:05:57.719
MIKE: They're not clowns.

817
01:05:57.753 --> 01:05:59.455
They're some
kind of animal
from another world

818
01:05:59.488 --> 01:06:01.557
that just look like clowns.

819
01:06:02.924 --> 01:06:06.428
Shit. Dave.
Dave. maybe they're
the ancient astronauts

820
01:06:06.461 --> 01:06:08.697
that came to our
planet centuries ago.

821
01:06:08.730 --> 01:06:12.134
and our idea
of clowns just
comes from them.

822
01:06:12.168 --> 01:06:14.202
PAUL: How come
they're not funny?

823
01:06:14.236 --> 01:06:16.238
RICH: Maybe they're
from a dying planet.

824
01:06:16.271 --> 01:06:18.540
Maybe their sun pooped out
and they need a new place
to live.

825
01:06:18.573 --> 01:06:19.942
PAUL: Maybe they're
using us for experiments

826
01:06:19.975 --> 01:06:22.644
to dissect and study.

827
01:06:22.678 --> 01:06:25.481
DAVE: So that means
they're intelligent.

828
01:06:25.514 --> 01:06:27.316
So why don't they
communicate with us?

829
01:06:27.349 --> 01:06:30.319
I mean. talk to us
instead of killing us?

830
01:06:30.353 --> 01:06:32.955
Maybe they're just
cruising through
the galaxy

831
01:06:32.988 --> 01:06:35.424
and stopped here
for a bite to eat.

832
01:06:38.627 --> 01:06:42.831
Yeah. Look. everybody. let's
just hold off on the talking.
okay?

833
01:06:42.864 --> 01:06:45.101
Let's not give
ourselves away.

834
01:06:46.301 --> 01:06:47.503
RICH:
What are we gonna
do when we find them?

835
01:06:47.536 --> 01:06:48.604
PAUL: Can we kill them?

836
01:06:48.637 --> 01:06:51.240
DAVE: Yeah.
You shoot them in the nose.

837
01:07:01.116 --> 01:07:02.485
Hey. watch this.

838
01:07:04.587 --> 01:07:05.688
Cool.

839
01:07:30.379 --> 01:07:32.214
(HORN SOUNDING)

840
01:07:32.248 --> 01:07:32.248
What happened?

841
01:07:32.248 --> 01:07:33.682
What did you do?

842
01:07:33.715 --> 01:07:35.818
I didn't do anything.

843
01:07:35.851 --> 01:07:36.919
Don't touch
anything. okay?

844
01:07:36.952 --> 01:07:39.455
This place is
probably booby-trapped.

845
01:07:45.060 --> 01:07:47.062
All right. now.
look. you guys.
stay together.

846
01:07:47.096 --> 01:07:48.564
I don't want to run
around and find you.
too.

847
01:07:48.597 --> 01:07:50.766
No problem.
We can handle it.

848
01:07:51.200 --> 01:07:52.568
Yeah. Okay.

849
01:08:00.075 --> 01:08:02.610
All right. let's go.

850
01:08:02.644 --> 01:08:05.714
Where'd they go?
Come on. Rich. Paul.

851
01:08:06.915 --> 01:08:08.216
Don't worry about
the Terenzi brothers.

852
01:08:08.250 --> 01:08:09.918
They do this all the time.

853
01:08:09.951 --> 01:08:13.622
Those guys are like cats.
They always land on
their feet.

854
01:08:13.656 --> 01:08:15.624
(BOTH GROANING)

855
01:08:34.209 --> 01:08:35.811
Are you Debbie's roommates?

856
01:08:36.810 --> 01:08:38.580
MIKE: Wait a second.

857
01:08:40.415 --> 01:08:43.419
I recognize this place.

858
01:08:43.452 --> 01:08:46.755
This is the tent that
Debbie and I were in.
Come on!

859
01:08:55.029 --> 01:08:56.464
Go. Mike.

860
01:09:09.010 --> 01:09:11.313
Okay.
this is where
we were before.

861
01:09:11.345 --> 01:09:13.447
This is incredible.

862
01:09:13.482 --> 01:09:15.484
Looks like they
got the whole town.

863
01:09:15.518 --> 01:09:18.721
We got to find her.
What color balloon
was she in?

864
01:09:20.287 --> 01:09:21.555
Yellow.

865
01:09:21.590 --> 01:09:22.925
All right.

866
01:09:37.939 --> 01:09:37.939
See anything. Mike?

867
01:09:37.939 --> 01:09:40.309
No.

868
01:09:45.680 --> 01:09:47.415
This is impossible. Mike.

869
01:09:59.361 --> 01:10:01.230
Quiet. Move back.

870
01:11:33.221 --> 01:11:34.490
(BELCHES)

871
01:11:47.836 --> 01:11:49.604
Paul was right. man.
They're hungry.

872
01:11:49.637 --> 01:11:50.672
They're gonna
eat everybody. man!

873
01:11:50.705 --> 01:11:52.808
Just calm down.
Just calm down.
all right?

874
01:11:52.841 --> 01:11:56.245
We got to find Debbie
before it's too late.
All right?

875
01:11:58.413 --> 01:12:01.250
Hey. that's the one.
The yellow balloon.
Is she in there?

876
01:12:01.983 --> 01:12:03.051
MIKE: Yeah.
she's in there!

877
01:12:03.084 --> 01:12:04.286
Debbie!

878
01:12:04.319 --> 01:12:04.319
She's alive.

879
01:12:04.319 --> 01:12:05.553
Thank God.

880
01:12:05.587 --> 01:12:05.587
How do we
get her out of here?

881
01:12:05.587 --> 01:12:07.690
I don't know.

882
01:12:08.523 --> 01:12:09.724
Careful. Mike.

883
01:12:09.758 --> 01:12:11.160
MIKE: Damn it!

884
01:12:11.193 --> 01:12:13.595
Debbie. Honey.
Hang on a sec. Mike.

885
01:12:13.628 --> 01:12:15.063
Damn!

886
01:12:15.096 --> 01:12:15.096
What are you doin'?

887
01:12:15.096 --> 01:12:17.065
Just stand back. Mike.

888
01:12:17.099 --> 01:12:18.233
You can't shoot.
You could kill her.

889
01:12:18.267 --> 01:12:21.236
Just back off. all right?
Now. just get ready to run.

890
01:12:24.973 --> 01:12:26.608
DAVE: Are you all right?

891
01:12:29.310 --> 01:12:30.779
Are you okay?

892
01:12:31.246 --> 01:12:32.514
Yeah.

893
01:12:33.615 --> 01:12:34.816
I couldn't breathe.

894
01:12:34.850 --> 01:12:37.219
It's okay.
Mike. hang on to
her for a second.

895
01:12:37.252 --> 01:12:38.386
God.

896
01:12:38.419 --> 01:12:40.555
We got to get
the hell out of here.

897
01:12:40.589 --> 01:12:41.789
Come on. Debbie. Come on.

898
01:12:41.823 --> 01:12:43.058
Come on.

899
01:12:48.096 --> 01:12:50.565
DAVE: Wait a second. guys.
We can't leave.

900
01:12:50.598 --> 01:12:52.501
There might be other people
still alive in these balloons.

901
01:12:54.803 --> 01:12:56.671
MIKE: Come on.
it's too late!

902
01:12:56.705 --> 01:12:58.173
DEBBIE: Dave!

903
01:13:06.048 --> 01:13:07.383
Shoot him!

904
01:13:09.184 --> 01:13:10.218
This way. Come on.

905
01:13:10.251 --> 01:13:11.820
Yeah. come on.

906
01:13:30.438 --> 01:13:31.506
What now?

907
01:13:31.540 --> 01:13:33.108
Everybody. down.

908
01:13:33.141 --> 01:13:33.141
We don't know
what's down here.

909
01:13:33.141 --> 01:13:34.375
Come on. Mike.

910
01:13:34.409 --> 01:13:36.378
Nobody's gonna put me
in a balloon again.

911
01:13:38.880 --> 01:13:40.115
Come on. Mike.
Get a move on!

912
01:13:48.524 --> 01:13:50.659
How come you guys
stopped here?

913
01:13:50.692 --> 01:13:52.060
(GROWLING)

914
01:13:52.093 --> 01:13:53.495
Good reason.

915
01:13:53.529 --> 01:13:54.763
MIKE: Okay.
which way do we go?

916
01:13:54.796 --> 01:13:55.864
That doesn't really matter.

917
01:13:55.897 --> 01:13:56.931
Let's go down here.

918
01:13:56.965 --> 01:13:58.133
DAVE: All right.
come on.

919
01:13:58.167 --> 01:13:59.635
(CACKLING)

920
01:14:10.946 --> 01:14:12.080
DAVE: Come on.
let's try in here.

921
01:14:12.114 --> 01:14:13.615
DEBBIE: No!

922
01:14:24.126 --> 01:14:25.627
DAVE: Come on.

923
01:14:26.061 --> 01:14:27.429
Be careful.

924
01:14:43.178 --> 01:14:44.413
Come on.

925
01:15:00.562 --> 01:15:01.997
MIKE: Shit!
Another door!

926
01:15:02.030 --> 01:15:03.365
DEBBIE: I can't
take this anymore!

927
01:15:06.734 --> 01:15:08.637
Come on.
open the door!

928
01:15:09.104 --> 01:15:10.205
Another door!

929
01:15:10.239 --> 01:15:12.107
Come on. Mike!

930
01:15:12.140 --> 01:15:13.609
Another door?

931
01:15:16.778 --> 01:15:16.778
Another door?

932
01:15:16.778 --> 01:15:18.380
Hurry!

933
01:15:22.851 --> 01:15:24.453
Debbie. come on!

934
01:15:27.155 --> 01:15:28.190
Dave. come on!

935
01:15:28.223 --> 01:15:29.858
(BALLOON BARKING)

936
01:15:31.692 --> 01:15:33.695
DAVE: Get the door.
Mike!

937
01:15:34.429 --> 01:15:34.429
Come on.

938
01:15:34.429 --> 01:15:36.398
DEBBIE: Here. here.

939
01:15:37.899 --> 01:15:39.635
DAVE: Come on. God.

940
01:15:40.935 --> 01:15:42.437
Thank God.

941
01:15:47.542 --> 01:15:50.979
Look at this place.
Where do we go now?

942
01:15:52.614 --> 01:15:54.349
Come on. let's go.

943
01:15:55.684 --> 01:15:57.452
(DEBBIE SCREAMS)

944
01:16:13.000 --> 01:16:15.937
Everyone. up on top.
Come on. let's move!

945
01:16:15.971 --> 01:16:17.506
MIKE: Come on!

946
01:16:17.973 --> 01:16:19.675
DEBBIE: Hurry!

947
01:16:45.400 --> 01:16:46.634
Hey. Rich. Paul!

948
01:16:46.667 --> 01:16:49.437
 PAUL:  Stop!
  Leave them alone!

949
01:16:49.470 --> 01:16:51.373
 Do what I say or else!

950
01:16:53.642 --> 01:16:55.276
 Give me the mike!

951
01:16:55.309 --> 01:16:58.980
  I am the great
  and powerful Jojo!

952
01:16:59.013 --> 01:17:01.249
 I command you to stop.

953
01:17:01.283 --> 01:17:04.519
  Do not hurt them.
  Let them go.

954
01:17:04.552 --> 01:17:07.055
  You will obey.
  Let them go.

955
01:17:07.088 --> 01:17:08.490
Now's our chance.

956
01:17:08.523 --> 01:17:10.425
(PAUL AND RICH ARGUING)

957
01:17:15.297 --> 01:17:17.766
MIKE: Rich! Paul!
Man. am I glad to
see you guys!

958
01:17:17.799 --> 01:17:19.567
Come on. let's go!
Get in the truck!
Let's go.

959
01:17:19.600 --> 01:17:20.635
Come on. Mike.

960
01:17:20.668 --> 01:17:22.370
Come on. Debbie.

961
01:17:22.403 --> 01:17:22.403
Come on. Rich!

962
01:17:22.403 --> 01:17:24.005
I'm tryin'!

963
01:17:24.039 --> 01:17:24.039
Turn it the right way!

964
01:17:24.039 --> 01:17:25.474
I am!

965
01:17:26.775 --> 01:17:28.175
Come on. Rich!

966
01:17:28.209 --> 01:17:29.745
Pull the choke.
Pull the choke.

967
01:18:04.612 --> 01:18:06.381
What the hell is that?

968
01:18:10.852 --> 01:18:13.555
(ROARING)

969
01:18:13.588 --> 01:18:15.457
I don't want to
play here anymore.
Can we go home now?

970
01:18:17.425 --> 01:18:19.226
Let's
make a run for it.
Just get out of here.

971
01:18:19.260 --> 01:18:20.962
Everyone out
of the truck!
Come on.

972
01:18:20.996 --> 01:18:22.597
We can't!
It's rented!

973
01:18:27.001 --> 01:18:28.503
(HORN BLARING)

974
01:18:33.008 --> 01:18:34.409
(ROARING)

975
01:18:35.210 --> 01:18:36.445
(BOTH SHOUTING)

976
01:19:02.403 --> 01:19:03.438
Hey! Rich! Paul!

977
01:19:03.472 --> 01:19:04.873
No. Mike. Mike!
It's too late. bud.

978
01:19:06.374 --> 01:19:07.642
(ROARING)

979
01:19:13.147 --> 01:19:15.250
DAVE: Look.
there's a way out now.

980
01:19:15.283 --> 01:19:17.785
Mike. take Debbie.
Get her out of here.
I'll draw its attention.

981
01:19:17.819 --> 01:19:20.222
No! Dave. don't!
We can all make it!

982
01:19:20.255 --> 01:19:21.423
We can't. Debbie.

983
01:19:21.456 --> 01:19:21.456
Stop it!

984
01:19:21.456 --> 01:19:22.590
Get her out of here. Mike!

985
01:19:22.624 --> 01:19:22.624
What are you doing?

986
01:19:22.624 --> 01:19:23.792
Now. Mike!

987
01:19:29.330 --> 01:19:31.767
Come on. guys. move!
Run for help!

988
01:19:34.035 --> 01:19:35.570
Over here!

989
01:19:57.892 --> 01:19:59.461
Come on.
you damn clown.

990
01:20:02.530 --> 01:20:03.999
Come on. you!

991
01:20:19.047 --> 01:20:20.315
MIKE: Come on!

992
01:20:20.348 --> 01:20:22.083
They're takin' off!

993
01:21:05.893 --> 01:21:07.462
(SHRIEKING)

994
01:21:57.445 --> 01:21:57.445
Dave!

995
01:21:57.445 --> 01:21:58.446
Dave!

996
01:22:01.516 --> 01:22:03.184
MIKE: You made it.

997
01:22:04.152 --> 01:22:05.921
You got them. man.

998
01:22:06.787 --> 01:22:08.923
(EXCLAIMS) What a ride!

999
01:22:08.956 --> 01:22:11.226
That's the last time
we let you drive.

1000
01:22:11.259 --> 01:22:12.360
You're alive!

1001
01:22:12.393 --> 01:22:13.527
Yeah.

1002
01:22:13.561 --> 01:22:16.263
But I saw
you guys get blown up
in the ice cream truck.

1003
01:22:16.297 --> 01:22:19.367
That. We hid in the
freezer with the
ice cream.

1004
01:22:19.401 --> 01:22:20.602
Yeah. Anybody
want a dip-sicle?

1005
01:22:20.635 --> 01:22:22.036
Oh. you and
